","meanings":["From the Greek name <i>Philippos</i>, meaning ‘lover of horses’, from <i>philein</i> ‘to love’ + <i>hippos</i> ‘horse’. This was popular in the classical period and since. It was the name of the father of  Alexander the Great . It was also the name of one of Christ's apostles, of a deacon ordained by the apostles after the death of Christ, and of several other early saints.  See also  Philippa ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Johan Philip Cloniger was born in 1665, in Siefersheim, Alzey-Worms, Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany, his father, Hans Velten Cloninger, was 25 and his mother, Apollonia, was 25. He married Mrs. Johann Philipp Cloninnger about 1687, in Cleebourg, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, France. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"1665–":"1665–Surnud","1660–Female":"1660–Surnud","1665–Male":"1665–Surnud","1670–1731":"1670–1731","1667–Female":"1667–Surnud","1695–1752":"1695–1752","1640–1684":"1640–1684","1640–1678":"1640–1678","1678":"1678","1667":"1667","1665":"1665","1731":"1731","1752":"1752","1695":"1695","1684":"1684","1640":"1640","1660":"1660","about 1687":"umbes 1687","1670":"1670","Cleebourg, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, France":"Cleebourg, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, Prantsusmaa","Siefersheim, Alzey, Rheinhessen, Hessen, Deutschland":"Siefersheim, Landkreis Alzey-Worms, Rheinland-Pfalz, Saksamaa","Siefersheim, Alzey, Rheinhessen, Hessen, Germany":"Siefersheim, Landkreis Alzey-Worms, Rheinland-Pfalz, Saksamaa"},"fi":{"1665–":"1665–Kuollut","1660–Female":"1660–Kuollut","1665–Male":"1665–Kuollut","1670–1731":"1670–1731","1667–Female":"1667–Kuollut","1695–1752":"1695–1752","1640–1684":"1640–1684","1640–1678":"1640–1678","1678":"1678","1667":"1667","1665":"1665","1731":"1731","1752":"1752","1695":"1695","1684":"1684","1640":"1640","1660":"1660","about 1687":"noin 1687","1670":"1670","Cleebourg, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, France":"Cleebourg, Bas-Rhin, Alsace, Ranska","Siefersheim, Alzey, Rheinhessen, Hessen, Deutschland":"Siefersheim, Landkreis Alzey-Worms